// Trabalho sobre filtro digital FIR
// Instrucoes basicas para utilizacao do program ISE da Xilinx // (valido para as versoes 14.x)
// Autor: Jose T. de Sousa
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

1. Open ISE Project Navigator.

2. Select File->New Project.

3. Enter Project Name and Location; click Next.

4. Select Family=Spartan3E, Device=XC3S100E, Package=CP132, Speed=-4, Preferred Language=Verilog; click Next; click Finish.

5. Select Project->Add Source; select all your .v files and the .ucf file; click Open.

6. On top of the Design window, select Simulation.

7. Select the testbench file.

8. In the Processes window expand ISim Simulator and double click on Behavioral Simulation.

9. If the simulator will not start, check the Console window for errors, click on the file links to open the respective files; fix the errors and go to step 8.

10. If the simulator starts but issues errors in its Console window, fix the errors and press the Relaunch button; repeat as necessary.

11. If the simulator issues the message "Finished circuit initialization process", press the Run All button.

12. You can select modules and drag the respective signals into the waveform window for visualization; then relaunch the simulator.

13. If the simulator stops at the $finish statement, the simulation is done.

14. On top of the Design window, select Implementation.

15. Right click on the module you wish to implement and select Set as Top Module.

16. In the Processes window double click on Generate Programming File.

17. In the Design Summary tab, explore the various reports produced by the tools, in order to extract the information you need.

18. Connect the FPGA board to your PC using the provided USB cable; switch on the board.

19. In the Processes window, double click on Configure Target Device; click OK.

20. Double click on Boundary Scan in the iMPACT Flows window; rigth click in the Bounday Scan tab and select Initialize Chain; click Yes.

21. Select the FPGA configuration file (.bit file) in your ISE project directory; click No; click Cancel; click Cancel.

22. Right click on the FPGA and select Program; the FPGA should be now ready to use.

Have Fun!

